channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Frank Biden Made Stunning Admission About Joe's Health Indicating We've Been Lied Toâ€”Then It Gets Weird
Manchin considers re-registering as Democrat to run for president
item.description: West Virginia Senator Joe Manchin, who switched from a Democratic Party member to an Independent, is considering switching back and running for president.

item.title: Trump Says Kamala Harris Will Be Easier to Defeat Than Biden
item.description: Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump said on Sunday he thinks Vice President Kamala Harris will be easier to defeat in November's election than Democratic President Joe Biden, who earlier in the day stepped aside as his party's candidate.

item.title: Joe Biden Stepped Down from His Campaign on National Ice Cream Day, Indicative of the Dem Party Meltdown
Forcing President Biden out of campaign may have been more about Congress than White House
item.description: What effect will President Biden's departure have on down-ballot races.

item.title: The Hill: Trump Holds 6-Point Lead Over Harris
item.description: Former President Donald Trump holds a six-point lead over Vice President Kamala Harris in The Hill's latest average polling.

item.title: Tulsi Gabbard Comes Back to Haunt Kamala Harris Again, Calls Her the 'Maidservant of Hillary Clinton'
RFK Jr says this is '2-man race' after Biden drops presidential bid
item.description: Independent presidential candidate RFK Jr. held a press conference on Sunday, shortly after President Biden dropped out of the campaign, saying "it's a two-man race."

item.title: Dems Promise 'Orderly Process' to Replace Biden, but Questions Remain
item.description: Shortly after President Joe Biden announced Sunday that he would drop his reelection campaign, Democratic National Committee Chair Jaime Harrison had a message: There would be no automatic coronation for his replacement."

item.title: So Soon? Hunter Biden Dismisses Suit Against Fox News Over 'Revenge Porn'
Trump calls for next presidential debate to be held on Fox News
item.description: Former President Donald Trump said Fox News should host the second presidential debate following President Biden dropping out of his race for a second term in the White House.

item.title: $46.7 Million Pours in for Harris, Dems
item.description: The Democratic Party is enjoying a fundraising boon following President Joe Biden's decision to drop out of the presidential race.

item.title: Grassley Demands Answers As Shocking New Info Revealed About Secret Service Resources for Jill Biden
Obama allies, advisers helped lead the charge among Dems looking to sink Biden ahead of official announcement
item.description: Allies of former President Obama called on President Biden to bow out of the 2024 presidential election in the lead-up to the president officially announcing he won't run.

item.title: Newsmax First Network to Report Biden Departure
item.description: Newsmax was the first to report on President Joe Biden's decision not to run for reelection.
